AnwigemA p. b. (licensor) is introducing a whole new concept in ship design.
With the revolutionary multi hull design from AnwigemA p. b. you will experience a more stable, safe and economic hull than traditional multi hulls like the Catamaran and Trimaran. 
This innovative design is suitable for recreational sailing and motor yachts and the professional industry as well.

A few benefits of the Trimonoran hull:
•	Gained speed till 30% when used in motor yachts;
•	Gained speed till 50% when used in sailing yachts;
•	Longer range due to (up to) 30% fuel savings;
•	Smaller fuel tanks are possible to save space and weight;
•	High stability for safe and comfortable sailing;
•	Large deck and hull space;
•	Relatively small drag;
•	Less water resistance than traditional mono hulls;
•	No need for a ballast weight;
•	Sea worthy design;
•	Relatively simple to realize the detailed design;

As mentioned above, the hull has what you need to use it for multiple purposes.
It can be used as a base for offshore crew transfer vessels, passenger ferries, pilot- and workboats, tenders and even super yachts after some more research.

The Trimonoran is so innovative it will disrupt the current market.
Herewith the ship designer, builder and owner may put their mark on the shipbuilding industry!
We are changing the industry now… Will you be joining us?

For more details go to www.AnwigemA.nl and contact us at:
phone: +31 (0)6 55 97 40 92 or info@AnwigemA.nl

Eerland Shiprepair B.V.: Excellence in Maritime Solutions Since 1976!

Since 1976, Eerland Shiprepair B.V. has established itself as a trusted name in the maritime industry. With decades of experience, we specialize in constructions, repair, and maintenance for seagoing and inland waterway vessels, delivering tailored solutions to meet the diverse needs of our clients.

𝐄𝐞𝐫𝐥𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐒𝐡𝐢𝐩𝐫𝐞𝐩𝐚𝐢𝐫 𝐁.𝐕. 𝐟𝐨𝐜𝐮𝐬𝐬𝐞𝐬 𝐦𝐚𝐢𝐧𝐥𝐲 𝐨𝐧:
• Ship repair at our yard, or on any site, national and international;
• Turn key solutions for both mobilisation and demobilisations of vessels;
• Underwater repairs with our own transportable docks & diving assistance by our partners;
• Certified welding of steel, aluminium, stainless steel and duplex constructions;
• On site repairs, like propeller/thruster change out and ship skin repairs, executed with our self-propelled 
crane barge ‘Marine Services 1’;
• Various vessel lay by services;
• Various machining & engineering services;
• Overhaul of winches.

Our shipyard is ISPS, ISO 9001 and VCA** certified. Located directly on the river Nieuwe Maas / Waalhaven in Rotterdam with open sea access.

To ensure good quality and service, Eerland Shiprepair B.V. offers the following equipment besides our skillful personnel:

• 110m long quayside with 14t SWL gantry crane and 240m free mooring length across our yard
• Construction hall with overhead cranes;
• Floating dock with 1400t lift capacity;
• 9.5t SWL dock crane and quayside facility;
• Mobile crane, Link-Belt RTC-8060 55-18.5t SWL;
• 13.6t, 5.5t & 2.5t SWL forklifts;
• Cherry picker;
