Limenda Shipbuilding Yard LLC was established on the basis of the Limenda Shipbuilding and Ship Repair Plant, founded in 1915 in the confluence of the Vychegda and Northern Dvina rivers in the south of the Arkhangelsk Region.
Due to its favorable geographical position the yard became a large North European ship building and repair center.
The city of Kotlas, in which the yard is located, is a major transportation hub on a railway connecting the center of the country with the oil and coal regions of the Komi Republic.
The yard has a waterways connection with the port of Arkhangelsk, then, through the White Sea and the White Sea-Baltic Canal with the Baltic Sea, as well as through the Sukhona River and the Mariinsky system with waterways of the Volga and North-Western basins.
Limenda Shipbuilding Yard LLC is a modern enterprise with well-equipped workshops and highly qualified staff. The key competences of the company are:
- shipbuilding;
- ship repair;
- metal structure products;
- engineering products;
- laboratory materials;
- energy.
Limenda Shipbuilding Yard LLC is focused on maximizing customer satisfaction and takes full responsibility for producing quality products in compliance with the terms of work.
Limenda Shipbuilding Yard LLC is an experienced producer of hulls and steel structures for several types of ships. We are currently able to offer our clients (which include, amongst other, OJSC Ilim Group, OJSC Severstal, divisions of OJSC Gazprom and Rosneft) best prices on the market along with flexibility of deliveries, without damage to the quality of our products.

